# filtering (NA exclusion, deduplication of Symbol)
table <- table[!is.na(table$Symbol)]   #remove rows with NA Symbol
# library(dplyr)
table_dedup <- table[,!c("ENSEMBL_ID")] %>% group_by(Symbol) %>% 
  summarise_all(median) %>% as.data.table()  # deduplication with summarising reads 

table_dedup[, Gene_id := table[match(table_dedup$Symbol, table$Symbol), "ENSEMBL_ID"] ]  # Add Gene_id ENSEMBL annotation because it was deleted
table_dedup[, Entrez := mapIds(org.Hs.eg.db, keys=Symbol, keytype="SYMBOL", column="ENTREZID")] # Add Entrez gene annotation
## 'select()' returned 1:many mapping between keys and columns
table_dedup$Entrez <- as.character(table_dedup$Entrez) %>% replace(list = table_dedup$Entrez == "NULL", values = NA)  # Replace NULL to NA
table_dedup <- table_dedup[!is.na(table_dedup$Entrez)] # Remove Entrez NA

# DEGs
de_mut.wt <- results(dds, contrast=c("Mutation", "mutant", "WT"), cooksCutoff = F)
de_mut.wt <- data.table(ID=rownames(de_mut.wt),as.data.table(de_mut.wt))
de_mut.wt. <- cbind(de_mut.wt,fData(es)) #ann
de_mut.wt. <- de_mut.wt.[order(de_mut.wt.$log2FoldChange, decreasing = TRUE), ]

de_mut.wt.degs.up <- de_mut.wt.[log2FoldChange > 1 & padj < 0.01]
de_mut.wt.degs.down <- de_mut.wt.[log2FoldChange < -1 & padj < 0.01]

de_mut.wt.degs <- rbind(de_mut.wt.degs.up,de_mut.wt.degs.down)

#order pathways, the sign(ES) function returns -1, 0, or 1 depending on whether ES is negative, zero, or positive, respectively. log(pval) computes the natural logarithm of the p-values, which is often used to transform p-values for better interpretability, especially when dealing with very small values.
# log(3.982271e-04) = -8
# log(3.982271e-07) = -15
mainPathways <- fp[pathway %in% Pathways$mainPathways][order(sign(ES)*log(pval)), pathway]
fpMain <- fp[match(mainPathways, pathway)] # From the table fp select only mainPathways
# Change ENTREZID to the SYMBOL in the column "leadingEdge"
fpMain[, leadingEdge := lapply(leadingEdge, mapIds,
                               x=org.Hs.eg.db, keytype="ENTREZID", column="SYMBOL")]
